
---


@startuml

' Define classes
class Customer {
    +String name
    +String contactInfo
    +List<Car> registeredCars
    +List<RideHail> rideHails
    +List<RideShare> rideShares
}

class Car {
    +String licensePlate
    +String make
    +String model
    +int year
    +boolean isSelfDriving
    +List<Customer> carOwners
    +List<RideHail> rideHails
    +List<RideShare> rideShares
    +List<Accident> accidents
}

class RideHail {
    +DateTime pickupTime
    +DateTime dropoffTime
    +Location pickupLocation
    +Location dropoffLocation
    +Duration duration
    +Distance distance
    +int numPassengers
    +double fee
    +String requestType (App / Wave)
    +Customer leadCustomer
}

class RideShare {
    +DateTime pickupTime
    +DateTime dropoffTime
    +Location pickupLocation
    +Location dropoffLocation
    +Duration duration
    +Distance distance
    +List<Customer> customers
    +double negotiatedFee
}

class Accident {
    +DateTime date
    +Location location
    +double damageAmount
    +Car involvedCar
}

class Location {
    +String address
    +double latitude
    +double longitude
}

' Relationships
Customer "1" -- "0..*" Car : registers
Car "1" -- "0..*" Customer : ownedBy
Customer "1" -- "0..*" RideHail : uses
Customer "1" -- "0..*" RideShare : uses
Car "1" -- "0..*" RideHail : provides
Car "1" -- "0..*" RideShare : provides
Car "1" -- "0..*" Accident : has
RideHail --> Location : pickupLocation
RideHail --> Location : dropoffLocation
RideShare --> Location : pickupLocation
RideShare --> Location : dropoffLocation

@enduml

---

### 🔍 Explanation of Classes and Relationships:

- **Customer**: Represents users of the Sober app or registered car owners. They can hail rides via the app or by hand-waving, and they may register their own cars.
  
- **Car**: Represents both self-driving cabs and user-registered cars. Each car can have multiple owners and be involved in multiple rides and accidents.

- **RideHail**: Represents individual ride-hailing trips. Includes details like time, location, passengers, and payment information.

- **RideShare**: Represents shared rides with multiple passengers. Includes negotiated pricing and list of all passengers.

- **Accident**: Stores information about any accident involving a car, including date, location, and damage amount.

- **Location**: A simple class to store geographic coordinates for pickup and drop-off locations.

---

### 📌 Notes:
- All classes are defined with basic attributes relevant to the system requirements.
- Relationships are modeled as associations using UML syntax.
- This diagram assumes that `Location`, `Duration`, and `Distance` are either value objects or simple types used within other classes.

